---
import MarketingLayout from '../../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
---

<MarketingLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="MakerVault privacy policy. Your files stay on your machine — we don't collect or transmit your design files.">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-2xl pt-24 pb-16">
    <h1 class="mb-8 text-center font-bold text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 7, 2026</p>

      <p>
        Thank you for using MakerVault. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy (the
        "Policy") describes the types of information MakerVault ("Company", "us", "we", or "our")
        may collect from you when you use the MakerVault desktop application, visit our website at
        makervaultapp.com (the "Website"), or use any related products, materials, and services
        (collectively, the "Services"). This Policy also describes our practices for collecting,
        using, maintaining, protecting, and disclosing that information.
      </p>

      <p>
        By accessing or using the Services, you agree to the terms of this Policy. If you do not
        agree, you should refrain from using the Services.
      </p>

      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        MakerVault is a local-first desktop application. Your design files, tags, notes, and metadata
        are stored entirely on your computer. We do not collect, transmit, or have access to your
        files or the data you create within the application. This Policy covers the limited
        information we do collect through licensing, our website, and communications with you.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Policy from time to time. If we make material changes, we will post the
        updated Policy on this page and update the "Effective Date" above. Your continued use of the
        Services after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the revised Policy. Please
        review this page periodically for updates.
      </p>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>Information You Provide to Us</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>License activation:</strong> When you activate a license key, we verify it with
          our licensing provider (LemonSqueezy). This transmits your license key and a device
          identifier (your computer's hostname and operating system). No file data is sent.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact form:</strong> If you contact us through our website, we receive the
          information you submit (such as your name, email address, and message).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Newsletter:</strong> If you subscribe to our newsletter or Windows launch
          notification, we collect your email address through our email service provider.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Purchase information:</strong> When you purchase MakerVault, payment is processed
          by LemonSqueezy. We receive your name, email address, and transaction details, but we do
          not collect or store your credit card or payment method details.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Update checks:</strong> MakerVault periodically checks for software updates via
          GitHub Releases. No personal data is sent during this check.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Website analytics:</strong> Our website may use basic analytics to understand
          traffic patterns. This may include your IP address, browser type, and pages visited.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Information We Do Not Collect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Your design files or their contents</li>
        <li>Your tags, notes, or metadata created within the application</li>
        <li>Usage analytics or telemetry from the desktop application</li>
        <li>Browsing or search history within the application</li>
        <li>Location information</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We may use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>To provide, maintain, and improve the Services</li>
        <li>To process your purchase and manage your license</li>
        <li>To respond to your comments, questions, and customer service requests</li>
        <li>To send you technical notices, updates, and support messages</li>
        <li>To send promotional communications, such as newsletters and product announcements (you may opt out at any time)</li>
        <li>To detect, prevent, or investigate security issues or fraud</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Share Your Information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information only in the following
        circumstances:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>LemonSqueezy:</strong> Payment processing and license management. Subject to
          <a href="https://www.lemonsqueezy.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LemonSqueezy's privacy policy</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>GitHub:</strong> Software update distribution via GitHub Releases.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Email service provider:</strong> If you subscribe to our newsletter, your email
          address is stored with our email service provider for the purpose of sending you
          communications.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal requirements:</strong> To comply with any court order, law, or legal process,
          including responding to any government or regulatory request.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Protection of rights:</strong> If we believe disclosure is necessary to protect the
          rights, property, or safety of the Company, our users, or others.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Business transfers:</strong> In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of
          all or a portion of our assets, your information may be transferred as part of that
          transaction.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>
      <p>
        All application data (file index, tags, notes, sources, preferences) is stored in a local
        SQLite database on your computer. We have no access to this data.
      </p>
      <p>
        For the limited information we do collect (license data, contact information), we take
        reasonable precautions to protect it. We have implemented technical, physical, and
        administrative security measures designed to reduce the risk of loss, misuse, unauthorized
        access, disclosure, or modification. However, no system can be guaranteed to be 100% secure,
        and any transmission of personal information is at your own risk.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes
        described in this Policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law. License
        activation records are retained for the duration of your license. Contact form submissions
        and email subscriptions are retained until you request removal.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Choices</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Newsletter:</strong> You may unsubscribe from promotional emails at any time by
          following the opt-out instructions in the email or by contacting us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>License deactivation:</strong> You may deactivate your license from within the
          application at any time, which removes the device association from our licensing provider.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Data deletion:</strong> You may request deletion of your personal information by
          contacting us at
          <a href="mailto:hello@makervaultapp.com">hello@makervaultapp.com</a>. We will respond to
          your request within 30 days.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The Services are not intended for children under 18 years of age, and we do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children under 18. If we learn that we have collected
        personal information from a child under 18, we will take steps to delete such information
        promptly.
      </p>

      <h2>Do Not Track Signals</h2>
      <p>
        Some web browsers have a "Do Not Track" feature. We do not currently respond to Do Not Track
        browser signals.
      </p>

      <h2>California Privacy Rights (CCPA/CPRA)</h2>
      <p>
        If you are a California resident, the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), as amended by
        the California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA), provides you with additional rights regarding your
        personal information:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Right to know:</strong> You have the right to request that we disclose the categories and specific pieces of personal information we have collected about you.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to delete:</strong> You have the right to request that we delete your personal information, subject to certain exceptions.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to correct:</strong> You have the right to request that we correct inaccurate personal information.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to opt out:</strong> You have the right to opt out of the sale or sharing of your personal information. We do not sell your personal information.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to non-discrimination:</strong> We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of your CCPA/CPRA rights.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:hello@makervaultapp.com">hello@makervaultapp.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Virginia Privacy Rights (VCDPA)</h2>
      <p>
        If you are a Virginia resident, the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (VCDPA) provides
        you with the following rights:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Right to access:</strong> You have the right to confirm whether we are processing your personal data and to access that data.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to correct:</strong> You have the right to request correction of inaccurate personal data.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to delete:</strong> You have the right to request deletion of your personal data.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to data portability:</strong> You have the right to obtain a copy of your personal data in a portable format.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to non-discrimination:</strong> We will not discriminate against you for exercising your rights under the VCDPA.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:hello@makervaultapp.com">hello@makervaultapp.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        The Services may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible
        for the privacy practices of those third parties. We encourage you to review the privacy
        policies of any third-party services you access.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy? Contact us at:
      </p>
      <p>
        Email: <a href="mailto:hello@makervaultapp.com">hello@makervaultapp.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</MarketingLayout>
